      "part_type": "Hadith",
      "path": "/books/al-kafi:2:1:97:17",
      "text": [
        " كُلَّمَا تَقَارَبَ هَذَا الْأَمْرُ كَانَ أَشَدَّ لِلتَّقِيَّةِ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Ibn Fazzal, from Ibn Bukeyr, from Muhammad Bin Muslim, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘Every time this matter (rising of Al-Qaim<sup>asws</sup>) comes closer, the (need for) dissimulation (<span class=\"iTxt\">Taqiyya</span>) intensifies’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "17. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from ibn Faddal from ibn Bukayr from Muhammad ibn Muslim from abu ‘Abd Allah (a.s.) who has said the following: “As it (time of Imam al-Mahdi) draws closer, al-Taqiyyah will be more intensely needed.” "
        ]
      }
